This paper discusses the impact of GDPR on web privacy, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cyber law and policy (cs.CY). The paper also evaluates the technical implementation of cookie consent notices, which could fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper analyzes the prevalence of cookie consent notices on popular websites, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) as websites often contain multimedia content.
